
## Errors

| Error Code | Description |
|------------|-------------|
| 401 | Unauthorized. The request did not include an Authorization token or the token was invalid. |
| 403 | Forbidden. The token does not have the necessary permissions to access the requested resource. |

## Implementation Notes

The API should be implemented in Laravel following the RESTful conventions. The service layer should be separated from the controller, following the Single Responsibility Principle.

The service layer should handle all the business logic related to providers, including fetching the providers from the database. The controller should only handle the HTTP request and response.

The pagination should be implemented using the built-in pagination in Laravel. The `links` object in the response provides the URLs for the first, last, previous, and next pages.

The API should be backward compatible with existing code. Any new features or changes should be added in a backward compatible way.
